REACT_NATIVE:

⚡️ GETTING STARTED:
There are two ways:
👉️ 1️⃣️ connect to your own mobile device, using QR code.
	[ 🔗️ https://reactnative.dev/docs/environment-setup?guide=quickstart ]
	
	< npx create-expo-app project_name >
	< cd AwesomeProject >

	< npx expo start >
 
 
👉️ 2️⃣️ Use a simulator(android or ios):
	- follow the steps in this link:
	[ 🔗️ https://reactnative.dev/docs/environment-setup?guide=native ]

⚡️ android studio:

- download & install android studio
- install JRC & JDK [ https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-java-with-apt-on-ubuntu-22-04 ]


npx expo install react-native-web@~0.19.6 react-dom@18.2.0 @expo/webpack-config@^19.0.0


⚡️ PREFERENCE of project creation (for simulator; but for device, ofcourse you have to use expo one): 
🧑‍💻️ < npx react-native@latest init AwesomeProject > over 🧑‍💻️ < npx create-expo-app AwesomeProject >

⚡️ DEVTOOLS:
- react native debugger: 🔗️ http://localhost:8081/debugger-ui/
- install react-devtools: 🧑‍💻️ npm i react-devtools --save-dev
- launch react-devtools: 🧑‍💻️ npx react-devtools

⚡️ TOOLS used:
	1️⃣️ react-navigation
		- react-native-screens
		- react-native-safe-area-context
		- npm install @react-navigation/native-stack
	
	
	
	
	
	

